Pause video now. Calculate the probability for craps to be rolled.

Many people like to bet the hardways. A hard way 6 bet says that you will roll a Hel before soft six Gl a Ed EJ a or 4 are rolled or a seven is rolled. You are betting you can roll the 6 the hard way, by getting “doubles”. If no 6 or 7 is rolled, the bet continues to be on. What is the probability for this to occur?

There is only one successful roll, but there are 4+6=10 unsuccessful, so the probability to win is 1/11. The house pays 9 chips plus your original chip if you win. Is this fair? How much should they pay to be fair?
